description.displayText: Francheska is a kindhearted individual who really loves kids. I can't thank her enough for how well she has taken care of our 5 month old baby girl. Always reliable. She is simply amazing!

description.displayText: I hired her for a night out with my wife to an event I was really looking forward to.  Unfortunately, Francheska didn't show up.  I called and texted her many times after she was scheduled to arrive, but I couldn't reach her.  I ended up calling a different babysitter on short notice and telling my wife to go on without me in the meantime.  My wife was able to make it to the event on time, but I missed most of it.

description.displayText: Francheska has been our son's nanny for the past 6 1/2 months and we could not be more pleased with how she treats him. She is patient, kind and always warm towards him (even when he has his tantrums)! My husband and I truly trust him being under her care. She plays with him, feeds him, changes diapers, cleans his laundry, buys groceries for him, brings him to gym, reads to him and takes him to the park for exercise and socializing. My husband and I both have demanding jobs and often require us to do overnight travel, she makes herself available for staying later in the evenings to give him his bath, brush his teeth and put him down for the evening. With egg and wheat allergies, she has had to deal with breakouts and knows how to handle such situations. She strikes a balance with professionalism and playfulness and we truly enjoy her presence in the household. She is an experienced caretaker with several years of child care. She is currently looking for weekend work to supplement her schedule. Any family would be lucky to have her care for their child/children.

description.displayText:
I've known Francheska for over a year now. She began working for us when our little boy was only three months old and she has continued to care for him until today at 18  months. During that time, she has done everything from spending a full-time week caring for him in our home, to date nights, daytime outings, and even a recent week in her own home day care when his regular daycare center was closed for a week for school year preparations. 

She has always been kind, caring, flexible, knowledgeable, and we will miss having her in our little one's life on a regular basis. As we are moving out of the area, we won't be able to utilize Francheska's services, but I recommend her highly for her very calm yet friendly way with children. Our boy took to her immediately and her affection for him is obvious both to us and to him, as he's happy to spend time in her company, playing, learning, and growing.
